# E-commerce API Testing Guide

## 1. Health Check
GET http://localhost:5000/health

## 2. User Registration (Creates profile in MongoDB)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "student@setec.edu",
  "password": "password123",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe"
}

## 3. User Login
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "student@setec.edu",
  "password": "password123"
}

## 4. Get All Products
GET http://localhost:5000/api/products

## 5. Add Item to Cart (requires token from login)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/cart/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "productId": "PRODUCT_ID_FROM_STEP_4",
  "quantity": 2
}

## 6. View Cart
GET http://localhost:5000/api/cart
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

## 7. Create Order (saves to MongoDB)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "items": [
    {
      "productId": "PRODUCT_ID_FROM_STEP_4",
      "quantity": 1
    }
  ],
  "shippingAddress": {
    "street": "123 SETEC Street",
    "city": "Phnom Penh",
    "state": "Phnom Penh",
    "zipCode": "12000",
    "country": "Cambodia"
  }
}

## 8. View My Orders
GET http://localhost:5000/api/orders/my-orders
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE